Caspian.

<span id="fn_300"></span>[58:9](sbe24033.htm#fr_304.md) Av. Takhmô-urupa,
the Tahmûras of the Shâhnâmah; he <span id="page_59">p. 59</span> is
said to have been a great-grandson of Hôshâng, whom he succeeded on the
throne, and to have reigned thirty years (see Bd. XXXI, 2, XXXIV, 4).
Written Takhmôrî*d*ŏ in TD2.

<span id="fn_301"></span>[59:1](sbe24033.htm#fr_305.md) See Râm Yt. 12,
Zamyâ*d* Yt. 29.

<span id="fn_302"></span>[59:2](sbe24033.htm#fr_306.md) Av. Yima khshaêta,
'Yim the [splendid](errata.htm#3.md);' he was a brother of his predecessor,
