but this period includes the lives of ten generations of his descendants
who did not reign (see Bd. XXXI, 14).

<span id="fn_317"></span>[61:5](sbe24033.htm#fr_322.md) He is said to have
been confined in Mount Dimâvand (see Bd. XXIX, 9).

<span id="fn_318"></span>[61:6](sbe24033.htm#fr_323.md) See § 20.

<span id="fn_319"></span>[61:7](sbe24033.htm#fr_324.md) The central region
